[141’2. W. by S.] [141’4. N.W.] Darlaston, 142’3. and a Fair on St. James Day; memorable for that King Wolpher (suppos'd to reside at Berry∣bank, a Hill adjoyning near Darlaston) here murther'd his two Sons Wulfald and Rufin, for embracing the Christian Faith.

