Aberconwey, 229’5. by Edw. 3d. Rais'd out of the Ruines of the old Brittish City Caer-baen, alias Canovium, seated on the Mouth of the Conway, imply'd by the prefixt Aber, i. e. Ostium Fluminis, a Large, Well∣built and fortified Town, Govern'd by an Alderman and 2 Bayliffs, with a Market on Frydays.

Hence by Charlecot Church on the Left and a Park on your Right which accompanies your Road for a Mile together,
