Andover 66’2. is seated on a Branch of the Test, a Town affording good Acco∣modation to Travellers, hath the Privilege of Electing Parliament Men; Enjoys a very great Market on Saturdays which is well stor'd with all sorts of Provision, &c. and hath 2 Fairs yearly, viz. May the 1st. and November the 6th.

