DIV3.P:
SEtting forward from Carmarthen,
Carmarthen, N.N.W. [3’3. N. W. b. W.] [the Account of which you have in Prestain to Carmar∣then, pag. 167.] you omit the forward Way on the Left to Haverford West, and bear∣ing to the Right, ascend at 5 Furlongs, and cross a Vale and 2 Rills, then you again ascend and cross another Vale, and in the Bottom a Rill, your Way being generally open, indiffe∣rently Arable and Pasture; at 3’5. you ascend an Hill of 4 Furlongs, and leave Llanell∣with Church some distance on the Left;
